SMALL Business Development Minister Khumbudzo Ntshavheni has been appointed to as an acting Minister in the Presidency following the death of Minister Jackson Mthembu. President Cyril Ramaphosa appointed Ntshavheni to take over the late Mthembu’s duties position until further notice The Presidency said in a statement that: “This appointment, in terms of Section 98 of the Constitution, follows the passing away of Minister in The Presidency Jackson Mthembu on Thursday, 21 January 2021, from Covid-19-related complications. “Minister Ntshavheni will continue to perform her responsibilities as Minister of Small Business Development while acting as Minister in The Presidency.” Mthembu was laid to rest on Sunday in his hometown of Emalahleni in Mpumalanga.